&gt;
&gt; Specification &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/css-values-4/#sign-funcs"&gt;https://www.w3.org/TR/css-values-4/#sign-funcs&lt;/a&gt; 
&gt;
&gt; Summary 
&gt;
&gt; The sign-related functions ​abs() and sign() ​compute various functions 
&gt; related to the sign of their argument. The abs(A) function contains one 
&gt; calculation A, and returns the absolute value of A, as the same type as the 
&gt; input: if A’s numeric value is positive or 0⁺, just A again; otherwise -1 * 
&gt; A. The sign(A) function contains one calculation A, and returns -1 if A’s 
&gt; numeric value is negative, +1 if A’s numeric value is positive, 0⁺ if A’s 
&gt; numeric value is 0⁺, and 0⁻ if A’s numeric value is 0⁻. The return type is 
&gt; a &lt;number&gt;, made consistent with the input calculation’s type.
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Blink component Blink&gt;CSS 
&gt; &lt;&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3ECSS%22"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/issues?q=customfield1222907:%22Blink%3ECSS%22&lt;/a&gt;&gt; 
&gt;
&gt; TAG review None 
&gt;
&gt; TAG review status Not applicable 
&gt;
&gt; Risks 
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Interoperability and Compatibility 
&gt;
&gt; None
&gt;
&gt;
